<br>
For example, there are some mobs that have a larger aggro range if their friends are attacked.  The gorangas in ME are one example.  There, you are better off trying to get within the aggro range of one, and let it aggro on you, than you are bow pulling.  <br>
<br>
It also depends on your level vs. the mob's level.  For instance, it's a lot easier to tag in Kael Arena from 58 up, you get a lot fewer adds on the tag.  <br>
<br>
You just have to experiment and change tactics to suit the situation.  And remember that it gets easier with mobs that you are used to tagging as you level up, and harder when you move into new zones with tougher mobs.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gnomos>Gnomos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 12:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3080.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tagging</span><hr size=1> Best way I've seen is to have an SK pull with darkness.  When they FD the snared mob won't go back, real easy to tag.  If you don't have an SK, try getting a cleric cast wake of tranquility on the pile of mobs, or other lull type spell, then tag.<br>
